'From Squeak2.9alpha of 17 July 2000 [latest update: #2549] on 31 August 2000 at 3:00:45 pm'!"Change Set:		betterEmbedDate:			31 August 2000Author:			Bob Arning- In certain cases HandMorph may not have an absolutely up-to-date menuTargetOffset (after a green dupe/drag, e.g.). HandMorph>>potentialEmbeddingTargets is enhanced to deal with that, but there may be other places this is also important."!!HandMorph methodsFor: 'world menu commands' stamp: 'RAA 8/31/2000 14:54'!potentialEmbeddingTargets	"Answer a list of targets into which the hand's arguement could be embedded"	| possibleTargets partsOfArgument where |	where _ menuTargetOffset.	partsOfArgument _ #().	argument ifNotNil: [		partsOfArgument _ argument allMorphs.		(argument bounds containsPoint: menuTargetOffset) ifFalse: [			where _ argument bounds center		].	].	possibleTargets _ self world morphsAt: where.	possibleTargets removeAllFoundIn: partsOfArgument.	^ possibleTargets! !